111843777.review:
I don't recommend this game even I am a fan of Record of Lodoss War.

1. Game is too short;
2. Repeat monster skills & boss skills;
3. Lack of depth for melee weapons(no combo & similar function);
4. Imbalance between melee weapons & magic(some bosses are easy to defeat by using will-o'-the wisp but extremely hard by using melee);
5. Basically no story.
6. Too expensive for the game quality.

The game is more like a Doujin game.

96919752.review:
I thought this game was amazing at first. Cool vibe, music, graphics, however;

It is insanely easy, and pretty short. It's like Symphony of the Night with 8% of the content. It just feels like a very linear version, with not much challenge. Wasn't expecting Ninja Gaiden Black level of difficulty, but I could probably beat this game with my feet. That aside, my first play through was fairly enjoyable.

Bigger issue, The most recent update made my game pretty much unplayable- it has severe lag, and I am just over it. Tried the V synch toggle, fullscreen adjustment, etc. It is just more trouble than it's worth. Another steam game that gets ruined for me during an update, and I don't the computer know how to undo such things. Waste of money.
